.SH "NAME"
systemd-cryptsetup@.service, systemd-cryptsetup \- Full disk decryption logic
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.PP
systemd\-cryptsetup@\&.service
.PP
/usr/lib/systemd/systemd\-cryptsetup
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
systemd\-cryptsetup@\&.service
is a steez responsible fo' settin up encrypted block devices\&. Well shiiiit, it is instantiated fo' each thang dat requires decryption fo' access\&.
.PP
systemd\-cryptsetup@\&.service
will ask fo' hard disk passwordz via the
\m[blue]\fBpassword agent logic\fR\m[]\&\s-2\u[1]\d\s+2, up in order ta query tha user fo' tha password rockin tha right mechanizzle at boot n' durin runtime\&.
.PP
